"'''Hutt and Seek'''" is a short story written by [[Chris Cassidy]] and [[Tish Eggleston Pahl|Tish Pahl]] which appeared in the ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' short-story anthology published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[December]] [[1999]]. It was originally scheduled to be published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 16|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 16]], but that issue was cancelled. It featured the characters [[Fenig Nabon]] and [[Ghitsa Dogder]] and was set in [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]].

==Plot summary==
The [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]]-and-[[Con artist/Legends|con-artist]] duo of [[Fenig Nabon]] and [[Ghitsa Dogder]] hire a pair of [[Mistryl Shadow Guard|Mistryl Shadow Warriors]], [[Shada D'ukal]] and [[Dunc T'racen]], to help them transport a cargo of [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Slavery/Legends|slave]] girls to [[Nal Hutta/Legends|Nal Hutta]]. The proud warrior [[Gender/Legends|women]] are put off by this unsavory assignment. The Shadow Warriors hijack the [[Starship/Legends|vessel]], eject Fenig and Ghitsa from the ship in an [[Escape pod/Legends|escape pod]], and return the Twi'lek slaves to [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]] – all of which is exactly what Ghitsa had hoped for when she hired them. With their cargo now [[Thief/Legends|stolen]], Ghitsa is able to report to her client and benefactor, [[Durga Besadii Tai|Durga the Hutt]], that the [[Karazak Slavers' Cooperative]] has stolen the Twi'leks. This allows Fenig and Ghitsa to leave Durga's employ and stir up trouble among slaving [[Crime lord/Legends|criminals]] while sparing the Twi'leks from slavery. 

==Continuity==
A news report within the story makes it clear that it occurred during the events of ''[[The Courtship of Princess Leia]]'' ([[1994]]), though early in the tale, [[Fenig Nabon|Fenig]] reflected on her two [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of partnership with [[Ghitsa Dogder|Ghitsa]]. That estimate should be closer to four years given the timing of the story "[[A Credit for Your Thoughts]]" ([[2000]]).<ref name="TERC" />

